        What Is an Auction Authority in Queensland and How Does It Differ from the Form 6?
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        Selling by auction in Queensland means signing two separate documents. Most sellers focus on one and overlook the other. Here's what each covers and what to check before you sign.
      </p>
